CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1778785872
OL,3,CMan behind bars after ramming a
OL,4,Cbulldozer into a village pub
OL,6,FMr Jason Howells, prosecuting,
OL,7,Fdescribed how Morgan left the bar
OL,8,Fsending text messages to the landlord,
OL,9,FChristopher Common, who had been
OL,10,Fsitting in a different area of the
OL,11,Fpub, stating: "Be careful, you can't
OL,12,Fstop a dozer" and "It'll be a drive-
OL,13,Fthru."
OL,15,FThe court heard that Morgan then
OL,16,Freturned to his and his father's yard,
OL,17,Fgetting into a large vintage Hanomag
OL,18,FD600 bulldozer. He drove off, damaging
OL,19,Fthe shed the bulldozer was stored in
OL,20,Fand driving over his brother's truck
OL,21,Fand in the direction of the pub.
OL,26,@sD@OOUtD@MO]tD@SOU
