CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1778785872
OL,3,CMan behind bars after ramming a
OL,4,Cbulldozer into a village pub
OL,6,FPanicked by what he saw, his father,
OL,7,FPhillip Morgan, drove after his son -
OL,8,Fwarning Mr Common to get everyone out
OL,9,Fof the pub.
OL,11,FMr Common and his wife told everyone
OL,12,Fto leave the pub, with one witness
OL,13,Fdescribing a "loud grinding noise" as
OL,14,Fthe bulldozer drove across the
OL,15,Fpavement and into the porch of the
OL,16,Fbuilding.
OL,18,FIt caused around #22,000 damage to the
OL,19,Fpub, plus lost earnings as they had to
OL,20,Fclose for that weekend.
OL,26,@uD@NOUuD@bO]
