OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1778785872
OL,3,CMan behind bars after ramming a
OL,4,Cbulldozer into a village pub
OL,6,FThe court heard that Morgan's actions
OL,7,Fthat night were completely "out of
OL,8,Fcharacter", that he was someone that
OL,9,Fwould help anyone in the village, and
OL,10,Fhis personal issues had affected his
OL,11,Fmental health.
OL,13,FIn defence, Mr Stephen Thomas, said
OL,14,FMorgan is genuinely remorseful for his
OL,15,Fbehaviour, with the defendant becoming
OL,16,Fvisibly upset as he appeared in court
OL,17,Fvia video link.
OL,26,@oD@\OUpD@JO]
